cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel framework for Estimation of Distribution Algorithms (EDA) to improve their performance in global optimization. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of probabilistic models and model complexity control in the proposed EDA framework. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with optimization algorithms and problem structure characterization. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a relevant category as the paper discusses the curse of dimensionality and the computational cost of traditional EDAs. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the benefits of understanding problem structure, which can be useful in control systems.
